    "text": "That's a promising signal, not just tea leaves — with one caveat about window size. Your 7-day average recovery of 66% now sits at the 66% you flagged as your green zone, while the 30-day average is still 61%, so the most recent week is doing the lifting. Six weeks of building volume with recovery drifting up rather than down is the pattern you want from a plan that fits — the usual failure mode runs the other way. The caveat: one good week can flatter the picture, so judge progress by the 30-day number catching up to the 7-day one. Focus for the coming two or three weeks: hold the current long-run progression steady and protect sleep on the nights after quality sessions. If the 30-day average climbs into the mid-60s too, you'll have stronger evidence that the plan fits.",
